SFS (SmartFoxServer) primarily used in older online flash games is a comprehensive -
SDK for rapidly developing multiplayer games and applications with Unity, HTML5, iOS, Android, Java, Universal Windows Platform, Adobe Flash/Flex/Air, C++ and more. 

Many people however are not aware the server is connected to with HTTP(?S) or either and TCP(SOCKET), enabling for easy connection from any 3rd party non gaming software, such as 
a traniner, modding tool or even exploiters.

An example for this is through the game produced by GoodGame Studios - Gangster, originally named Mafia.
During the time this game has been around not many actual hacks have existed for the game itself aswell as alot of softwares contains malware have been floated around on
the internet, either stealing your game login or infecting you whole computer.

